{"serial": "00092", "department_serial": 4, "code": "LN2010", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Life issues from English movies", "ch": "英文電影與社會議題"}, "notice": {"en": "Undergraduate course. Course level:upper intermediate. Unexcused first class absence will result in a reduction in grade. The lecturer reserves the right to withdraw students absent for the first 2 classes.", "ch": "中高級課程。大學部課程。分發條件:(1)非英美語文系。(2)第一次上課未出席，需事先跟 老師請假，否則扣學期總成績。(3)前兩週未出席者，老師有權退選該生。"}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chen, Jou-Yin"], "ch": ["陳若盈"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["6", "7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "O", "room": "314"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "語言中心", "en": "Language Center"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 3, "selected": 43, "remark": {"ch": "中高級課程。大學部課程。分發條件:(1)非英美語文系。(2)第一次上課未出席，需事先跟 老師請假，否則扣學期總成績。(3)前兩週未出席者，老師有權退選該生。", "en": "Undergraduate course. Course level:upper intermediate. Unexcused first class absence will result in a reduction in grade. The lecturer reserves the right to withdraw students absent for the first 2 classes."}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程為中高級英文課程\n1.能理解與整合電影文本的資訊如逐字稿與背景時空資訊。\n2.能搜集電影相關主題及整理資訊以支持論證\n3.能於小組討論時能有效地以英文溝通、辯論、以及做詳細的分析\n4.學習使用多種思考工具，拓展思考深度與廣度。\n5.能將課堂學習到的英文資訊整理及小組學習的經驗，延用到個人英文自學的規畫中", "en": "This course is designed for students with intermediate to advanced English proficiency.\nOn successful completion of this course, students will be able to\n1.Comprehend and synthesize information from movies, transcripts, and supplementary materials \n2.Conduct self-directed research as support for analysis and argument\n3.Communicate, debate, and give presentation of movie analysis.\n4.Familiarize with and apply several thinking routines (such as making connections, giving explanation and interpretation, reasoning with evidence, considering multiple viewpoints, empathizing and reflecting.)\n5.Apply the thinking skills and individual and group learning experience in personal learning."}, "outline": {"ch": "本課程意旨在利用電影的題材當作媒介，來增加英文聽說讀寫及批判性思考能力。上課會指定4-5部具有豐富人生及社會議題的電影，在看完指定電影前，學生必須先查電影相關資料，如故事大綱、角色介紹、製作背景；在看完電影後，依據學習單及教師指引的方向，運用多元思考工具，進行劇情摘要、角色分析、議題分析、連結文本與史實、連結電影與時事議題等等分析與討論。上課方式包括個人報告、小組討論、對話、簡報、表演等、學習歷程反思。\n**英文系學生若欲修課可email給教師討論修課動機再人工加選。\nrachelchen0105@gmail.com", "en": "In this class, English movies are used as the media to improve critical thinking skills. Students will be guided to explore their motivation and interest in digging out important issues from movies, and manage their own learning by previewing and exploring relevant movie materials. On one hand, students will improve their language ability by practicing listening and reading for main ideas, developing vocabulary, and conducting public speaking ＆ communication. On the other hand, students will be provided with multiple thinking routines to deepen their thinking ability in making interpretations, considering multiple viewpoints, reasoning with evidence, making connections among multiple information, reflecting on one’s own life experience, etc. Self-reflection will be highly valued in this class as a venue for transforming learning experience into personal life-long learning habits.\n**Exchange students or students from English Dept. may email the teacher to discuss about eligibility of taking this course."}, "textbook": {"ch": "*All of the assigned movies are on course reserve in the audio-video library already.", "en": "*All of the assigned movies are on course reserve in the audio-video library already."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100", "en": "100"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授", "en": ["Lecture"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "‧Attendance, participation, assignments  25％\n‧Report 1＆ 3 30％\n‧Midterm 15％\n‧Final presentation 20％\n‧Learning profile ＆ reflection 10％", "en": "‧Attendance, participation, assignments  25％\n‧Report 1 ＆ 3  30％\n‧Midterm 15％\n‧Final presentation 20％\n‧Learning profile ＆ reflection 10％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "週一1-3 pm、週四9-10am", "en": "1-3 pm, Mon; 9-10 am Thurs."}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "期末考於學期第16週舉行；考試完後無須到班，唯需於第17-18週撰寫並於第18週繳交learning portfolio.", "en": "Final sentation is held in Week 16. There won't be meeting in class in Week 17 & 18. Students will have to turn in their learning portfolio by the end of Week 18."}, "domain": {"ch": "應用英文\n\n\n、\n\n\n文化與社會", "en": "應用英文\n\n\n、\n\n\n文化與社會"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "語言溝通", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現", "作品/創作展演"]}, {"competencies": "文化視野", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "作品/創作展演"]}, {"competencies": "自主學習", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["專題研究報告(書面)", "學習檔案評量"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Language & Communication Skills", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Research Report(printed on paper)", "Attendance/Performance", "Products/Creative Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Intercultural Literacy", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Products/Creative Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Self-directed Lifelong Learning", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Research Report(printed on paper)", "Portfolios Assessment"]}]}, "assignCriteria": {"ch": ["學制:限學士班。系所:限非英美語文學系。"], "en": ["Type:Undergraduate Program only.Department:Non-Department of English only."]}, "preselecStu": 26, "stuGender": {"male": 17, "Female": 26}, "stuGrade": {"doctor": {}, "master": {}, "bachelor": {"4": 15, "3": 13, "2": 13, "1": 2}}, "stus": [{"serial": "1", "stunum": "10*******", "department": "財務金融學系", "grade": "4", "class": "*", "priority": "2", "isRequired": false, "isPreselected": false, "isManuallySelected": false, "isCodeSelected": false}, {"serial": "2", "stunum": "10*******", "department": "文學院學士班", "grade": "4", "class": "*", "priority": "1", "isRequired": false, "isPreselected": true, "isManuallySelected": false, "isCodeSelected": false}, {"seria